tinction curve, as previously found toward GRB 071025, provides a better fit for only two of the afterglow SEDs. However, because of the lack of highly extinguished sight lines and the limited wavelength coverage we cannot distinguish between the different scenarios. For the first time we also report a photometric redshift of z phot = 7.88 -0.94 +0.75 for GRB 100905A, making it one of the most distant GRBs known to date.},
