ith an extreme threshold of Z& = 0.1 Z0 are excluded at z < 1. Under a very basic assumption, we estimate that the LGRB rate can directly trace the SFR starting from z $\sim$ 4 and above. Conclusions. GRB hosts at z < 1 have lower luminosities and stellar masses than expected if LGRBs were unbiased star formation tracers. The use of the Swft/BAT6 complete sample keeps this result from being affected by possible biases that could have influenced past results based on incomplete samples. The preference for low metallicities (Z < 0.5 Z0) inferred by the comparison with the simulations can be a consequence of the particular conditions needed for the progenitor star to produce a GRB. [ABSTRACT FROM AUTHOR]},
